================================================================================
NOTICE - Brother QL Label Printer Library
================================================================================

This software is a derivative work based on the original brother_ql library.

Original Work:
--------------
Project: brother_ql
Author: Philipp Klaus
Copyright: (C) 2016-2023 Philipp Klaus and contributors
License: GPL-3.0-or-later
Source: https://github.com/pklaus/brother_ql

Modified Work:
--------------
Organization: Luxardo Labs
Copyright: (C) 2025 Luxardo Labs
License: GPL-3.0-or-later (same as original)

Major Changes in This Fork:
----------------------------
1. COMPLETE MODERNIZATION
   - Python 3.13+ only (removed all Python 2 compatibility)
   - Full type hints and mypy compliance
   - Modern Python patterns throughout

2. ARCHITECTURE REDESIGN
   - Removed all backends (600+ lines of code)
   - Simplified to just 10 core Python files
   - JSON-based configuration for labels and models
   - Direct device writing instead of complex backend system

3. IMPROVED LABEL POSITIONING
   - Fixed 23x23mm label centering on QL-810W
   - Added positioning override system via JSON
   - Support for full-bleed printing on die-cut labels
   - User-adjustable offset parameters

4. ENHANCED IMAGE PROCESSING
   - Better Floyd-Steinberg dithering
   - Improved rotation handling
   - Red/black separation for QL-8xx series
   - Proper monochrome conversion

5. COMPREHENSIVE TESTING
   - Complete pytest test suite (48 tests)
   - Tests for all major functionality
   - No experimental code in main library

Core Files (brother_ql/):
-------------------------
- __init__.py - Package exports with examples
- conversion.py - Main convert() function
- raster.py - BrotherQLRaster protocol implementation
- image_processing.py - Image manipulation and dithering
- label_positioning.py - Centering and alignment logic
- labels.py - Label specifications from JSON
- models.py - Printer model specifications from JSON
- constants.py - Protocol constants
- enums.py - Type-safe enumerations
- exceptions.py - Error types
- config/labels.json - Label definitions
- config/models.json - Printer specifications with positioning

Attribution:
------------
The Brother QL raster protocol implementation is based on the reverse
engineering work by Philipp Klaus and contributors to the original
brother_ql project. The core protocol commands remain largely unchanged.

This fork focuses on modernization, simplification, and fixing specific
issues with label positioning, particularly for the QL-810W printer.

